Sibanye-Stillwater miners are still camped outside the Union Buildings in Pretoria. They want President Cyril Ramaphosa to address their issues. The workers have been on a wage strike for over 4-months now . eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has the latest from the Union Buildings. #DStv403 PRETORIA - The Sibanye-Stillwater miners are still camped outside the Union Buildings in Pretoria. They say they will not move until President Cyril Ramaphosa intervenes in their protracted wage dispute. READ: Sibanye-Stillwater employees camp outside Union Buildings Ramaphosa vowed to deal with workers' grievances at Cosatu's May Day rally. Now, mineworkers are holding him to that promise. WATCH: Sibanye Stillwater strike | Mantashe's mining rights threats They want his intervention in a four-month-long wage strike. Workers are demanding a 6 percent salary increase but the mine says the demand is not sustainable.